CEBU CITY, Philippines ‚Äî Minors aged 15 years and below can now go out in Cebu City provided they are accompanied by fully vaccinated guardians. This was the pronouncement of Acting Mayor Michael Rama as signified in the new Directive 10-25-01 setting the guidelines for the implementation of the Alert Level 2 quarantine status in the city. Generally, the stay-at-home order remains for minors below 15 years old, senior citizens above 65 years old, and people with comorbidities or pre-existing medical conditions, except for obtaining essential goods and services, for work, and other permitted activities. Since the last Executive Order, senior citizens above 65 years old may already go out as long as they are fully vaccinated. This time, the Cebu City government has allowed minors below 15 years old to also enjoy the opening of more establishments in the city, and the policy also serves as a prelude to the eventual return of the face-to-face classes. ‚ÄúSubject to other legal restrictions, minors and children who are below 15 years of age may be allowed in authorized establishments. Provided that they must be accompanied and supervised by a parent, guardian, or responsible adult.‚Äù ‚ÄúMinors need not be accompanied for purposes of obtaining essential goods and services,‚Äù stated the directive. Furthermore, minors can enter authorized establishments such as indoor dining, as long as they are accompanied by a fully vaccinated guardian.

A few weeks ago we pulled sweet boy Brees from a rural shelter.  2 ER visits and a stay at the vet and we had no answers why he was so sick. 3 negative parvo tests.  Brees passed away with his foster by his side in tears. We sent a sample off for more accurate testing. He had parvo. Unfortunately Brees came from a shelter that does not receive funding for vaccinations or any medical at all. 

We want to help the shelter at least try to prevent a similar situation for any dog that enters their facility. They only have 8 dog runs. If they can vaccinate them as soon as they arrive it will lessen the chance of another going through the same as Brees.  

We have ordered 25 puppy vax, 25 adult vax and 25 bordetella vax, needles/syringes and dewormer and syringes. This is a start. We will be working on more for this shelter, but we need YOUR help. 

PLEASE consider a donation to help us help them. 

PayPal.me/fwabandoned 
Venmo: @fwabandoned

Good morning. I finally received a response from CDPHE regarding some of your questions. I hope you find the information helpful. The Q and A are below. -Chelsea Brentzel, KRDO Q: ""When a Pfizer or Moderna vaccine is no longer valid, what happens to those chemicals? Should I be afraid of what was administered into my body? Can a vaccine that was not handled per the temperature guidelines become dangerous when administered to a patient?"" CDPHE: The current data show that there is no risk for the patient to become sick from an invalid vaccine. Failure to store and handle vaccines properly can reduce vaccine potency, resulting in inadequate immune responses in patients and poor protection against disease. Q: ""My Dr. Moma vaccine shot is 100% potent. It was handled with correct temperature controls throughout the supply chain. However, I am still being told to restart the vaccine process."" CDPHE: There is no documentation supporting that the Dr. Moma clinic maintained the required cold chain of the vaccines. The most important thing to know is that it‚Äôs ultimately up to the patient to decide what to do about revaccination. CDPHE‚Äôs revaccination guidance is based on consultation with medical experts at the CDC. Q: ""Over a nine week period, I will have received three total vaccines, all of which are 100% potent and viable. What are the risks of this situation? Is there such a thing as ""vaccine overdose?"" Can my body overproduce antibodies? Can my side effects from the 3rd shot be extreme? What are the short and long-term consequences I should consider?"" CDPHE: CDPHE consulted with the CDC and released guidance for patients who were vaccinated at Dr. Moma‚Äôs clinic. We believe this is the best guidance to ensure patients are protected. If you have specific questions about receiving a third dose, we encourage you to also speak with your healthcare provider. Q: ""We, the FB group seeing conflicting info about advice on 3 shots, some local docs say no, some yes. I am getting 3rd shot next week, following CDC guidelines, can they CDPHE provide anything in writing, like a study, defending that decision. So far, all the studies we‚Äôve seen have the 3rd shot given 6 months from later, not 21 days"" CDPHE: Both Pfizer and Moderna are currently studying the safety and effectiveness of booster doses. There is a difference between receiving a booster dose 6 months after a valid two-dose series, and receiving additional doses as part of revaccination following invalid previous doses. CDPHE consulted with the CDC and released guidance for patients who were vaccinated at Dr. Moma‚Äôs clinic. We believe this is the best guidance to ensure patients are protected. Q: ""Biggest worry is if manufacturers got mixed together. I had two shots, my card pre-filled out at reception, then I could take my pick of injection rooms, and apparently both shots given out in each room. 1st shot 3/20, 2nd 4/9, about an hour before shut down"" CDPHE: Patients should have received two doses of the same vaccine. If someone did receive one of each, they should plan to receive one additional dose of the same type of vaccine as their most recent dose. If their second dose was Moderna, they should receive another Moderna dose at least 28 days after your second dose. If their second dose was Pfizer, they should receive another Pfizer vaccine at least 21 days after your second dose. The safety and efficacy of a mixed-product vaccine series have not been evaluated, and should be approached cautiously. In exceptional situations in which the vaccine product given for the first dose cannot be determined or is no longer available, any available mRNA COVID-19 vaccine may be administered at a minimum interval of 28 days between doses to complete the mRNA COVID-19 vaccination series. If, for some exceptional reason, you receive a different product for your second dose, you do not need to repeat the vaccination again with additional doses. In the event individuals receive a different second dose under exceptional circumstances, no additional precautions are necessary. In the case of the Dr. Moma clinic, if individuals do not know what vaccine they received, they can receive either mRNA vaccine as part of revaccination. Q: ""What do we do with vax cards? Mine shows two shots, by next week 3...can we get guidance from CDPHE on if/how these will be accepted by industry, like airlines?"" CDPHE: We expect vaccine cards will still be valid with three doses shown on the card. Q: ""Has anyone seen her cold storage, and are there really logs"" CDPHE: CDPHE has obtained a copy of the clinic‚Äôs paper temperature logs and received photos of the clinic‚Äôs vaccine storage unit. At the on site visit, they did not have a digital data logger for recording the vaccine storage unit‚Äôs temperatures, as required. Q: ""Why has CDPHE been so absent in assisting us with our questions. Thankful for our local journalists, doing their job for us. CDPHE is definitely in ‚Äúavoid a lawsuit‚Äù mode, (truncated)

If you go to the CDPHE website and search for ""Moma,"" you will get ZERO returns. Why is that? Interesting that they post a red banner regarding discontinuing J&J vax. Where is the red banner and links for those of us who have been injected with who-knows-what-efficacy and who have to be revaccinated? The CDPHE's silence is deafening. On another note, as soon as I received the email from the CDPHE (which, by the way, went to spam) telling us we needed to redo the protocol, I wrote them an email expressing my dissatisfaction and pointing out to them that in that very email, they had a link to a provider list - a pdf - and guess who was STILL on the list as a provider??? Dr. Moma! They have yet to even acknowledge my email to them, but I suspect they have read it because they removed that PDF! Sloppy and hiding behind their organizational machine, without acknowledging any shortcomings, IMHO.

If it's so temperature and record sensitive, why are they having so many damn people giving it out? Is the local grocery store doing things right? Now I don't know who to trust or what to do. And hi! Sorry we are in this boat of worry together.

Update post new CDHPE letter 4/21 - the CDHPE still says that testing won't tell you anything, but it seems to lump discussion of different types of tests together rather than discussing the different types individually and telling us specifically which ones do and don't provide useful information, which is unfortunate, as it does seem like there are tests that tell us what we need to know. I'm not a doctor. ;) So, take this post about these kinds of tests with whatever grains of salt you need to apply to it! It seems like rather than throwing their hands up in the air because of bad paperwork and guessing we all need third shots or two more shots, they give give us spike protein tests, which, according to this link from Quest Diagnostics, DO test if a vaccine was effective. National Jewish Hospital and other sources have similar information about this specific test. It has to be the right test; you can't get the generic ""did I have COVID"" antibody test. That one does not check for a vaccine's after effects. Read the link. Test: IgG and IgG/IgM antibody serology testing (https://www.questdiagnostics.com/home/Covid-19/HCP/antibody/) This would only make a difference if the health department is willing to then call a shot/s we've already received valid, ensure our info is in the database should that ever be required for travel or job purposes, and make sure our cards are okeydokey. Otherwise it's knowledge but you still don't have the paperwork, which is a stupid reason to have to get vaccinated, but travel and jobs are likely to require this administrative overhead. The health department texted me yesterday telling me I needed to get my second COVID vax. I guess this means they do have record of my first shot somewhere, but not my second one...saving me the trouble of making that record request. So there's that.

column30: Update 8 May (Sat) It took a while - but on Wednesday, about 16-18 hours after the 3rd vax (which was Tues PM) (a couple of hours after I wrote the first installation of this post) I got the ""hit by a truck"" feeling. It was hard to concentrate for work and my body hurt. I felt better by the time I woke up Thursday. Thursday was normal, energetic even, and I was moving boxes, etc. and work was fine. Then, I had a bad headache Thurs PM. TWO naps on Friday (I never nap) and start of GI issues. Nausea since last night and general blech feeling, but not really body aches. Vaccine effects or just a poorly timed bug picked up from a grocery store or something - who knows! But I was super surprised to have any effects at all after shot 3! 3rd Pfizer vaccine @ UCHealth yesterday. The first 2 were 3/19 and 4/8 @ Dr. Moma. Feel great - a mild ""feel like I have a cold"" reaction, but it could be allergies, too. My reaction to my first two shots seemed pretty standard to friends' and family's reactions, so I've likely had 3 good jabs now. UCHealth (on E Pikes Peak) was very fast and organized. They have lots of appointment availability if you need one. They were familiar w/the Dr. Moma situation. My nurse was a little unsure at first about how to treat a 2-Moma-shot ( 1 vs 2 more shots, and what to do with the card) but a quick consult with someone who seemed to be in charge cleared it up confidently. I knew what I needed, but he wanted to double-check to make sure he did everything right. I didn't mind. I now have a card with 3 shots listed and a card with just yesterday's listed, and I'm keeping both for now. The difference in site organization was stark!

I was there on 4/3 and it was complete chaos. Moma took my info and she gave me my Vax card before I entered the hallway to wait for my vaccination room. My card says Pfizer, but if they were giving both doses on the same day, how can I be certain I actually received Pfizer? She didn't know what room I would go into?

I‚Äôm not sure if this is helpful to anyone dealing in the insurance realm, but a state spokesperson just sent me this response when I asked about the insurance legality of billing for invalid vaccines. I will include as much of that info as I can in my report at 10:00 tonight on KRDO NewsChannel 13 / KRDO.com ‚ÄúAre they receiving these billing statements directly from Dr. Moma or from their insurance company? More explicitly, is this a bill from Dr. Moma directly, or is this an explanation of benefits (which is different than a bill) from their insurance company? Could you please send us all the examples of this you have received? And if your viewer is comfortable, can you send us their contact information? Our team would like to connect with them. The vaccine is free. Neither insurance companies nor providers can bill a patient for a COVID-19 vaccine regardless of the circumstance. Providers cannot ask anyone to pay for the vaccine or other administrative costs, regardless of their insurance status. Providers are not allowed to turn people away because of an inability to pay or current medical coverage status. When CDPHE is aware of a provider billing a patient for the COVID-19 vaccine, we contact that provider to let them know they cannot charge patients for vaccines. Anyone who has been inappropriately billed by a provider can call our vaccine hotline at 1-877-CO VAX CO or file a report. Concerns about fraudulent billing would be referred to other appropriate federal and or state agencies for further investigation. Generally vaccine providers can request reimbursement from a patient‚Äôs health insurance, but that provider should not bill the patient. And the insurance company should not bill the patient. If anyone believes that they are receiving a bill due to a problem with their insurance (e.g., the insurance is not paying the vaccine provider appropriately or on time, or the insurance company has made a mistake), the patient can contact the Colorado Division of Insurance to ask questions or file a complaint - 303-894-7490 / DORA_Insurance@state.co.us / doi.colorado.gov. If this communication is from their insurance company and asking for payment, the person can also file a complaint with the Colorado Division of Insurance. We are confident that the vast majority of COVID-19 vaccine providers are aware they cannot charge and are not trying to do so, and those who have inappropriately charged have reversed it once they became aware they cannot charge. ‚Äú

I will train you personally with how I like calls handled. -WiFi or cell service with data. -CashApp or PayPal to receive payments weekly. -a quiet work space. -available anytime between 8am-6pm EST to make calls based on time zones. -an email address to receive work. -willing to work alone at your own pace and keep in communication regularly with me. -a positive attitude. -must be in the USA and speak fluent English. column30: Hey guys. As a mom I have started a new business. I am looking for someone who is willing to help me cover outbound cold calls Monday-Friday. I am flexible. You can pick the hours you work daily. I get being a parent! I have a toddler and am expecting in April. (That‚Äôs why I need help with calls-my house is far from quiet!) Requirements: -comfortable on the phone or willing to learn. -you will need a smartphone to be able to access our phone dialing app. -ability to adapt to each phone call. This will not be traditional sales. I will train you personally with how I like calls handled. -WiFi or cell service with data. -CashApp or PayPal to receive payments weekly. -a quiet work space. -available anytime between 8am-6pm EST to make calls based on time zones. -an email address to receive work. -willing to work alone at your own pace and keep in communication regularly with me. -a positive attitude. -must be in the USA and speak fluent English. Not required: -No COVID vax required. You are working remotely and your health is your personal choice. I have no right to enforce something like this on you. -computer or laptop. This will make life easier on you, but you can do everything from you phone. -experience. It‚Äôs a plus, but not required. I am looking for something altogether different when it comes to call handling. These will not be rushed calls, but rather really getting to know the customer and their needs so that we can help them grow as well. The position will be long term with bonuses per contract that you close. It will be contract hourly without additional benefits. There will be a 2 week trial period for all new team members. Starting pay is $4/hour (including training) plus bonuses monthly at 1% or the total monthly account value for the first full 3 months of the account longevity. Raises are a big possibility as we grow. Minimum 10 hours per week, but you can work as much as you would like if there are contacts to reach out to. Please comment if you are interested and I‚Äôll message you.

This is absolutely about that conversation people are having about the Orange Madman‚Äôs inspired Jan. 6 insurrection. This includes the recent damning Senate report that incontrovertibly found that the ex-president illegally attempted to subvert the 2020 election. The right wing speaks as though nothing criminal happened; that Jan. 6 was a normal tourist visit by patriotic American citizens, exercising their Constitutional right to protest and peaceably assemble. They have been doing this while lionizing those that got arrested as ‚Äúpolitical prisoners.‚Äù All of it is farce, though tragi-comic is perhaps a better description, as their mentally diminished ‚Äúdear leader‚Äù keeps raking in the dough from his willing followers. The political class speaks of it as if it was but a protest-rally-riot that got slightly out of hand. And they speak of it as if it were in the past tense. Actually, it is not they that are speaking that way, but rather the actions of the prosecutors that are unambiguously communicating that message: They were mostly overzealous protestors, following their leader, not anti-American ‚Äúrevolutionaries.‚Äù Translation: good ol‚Äô American boys. The prosecutors are intent on securing low level convictions via plea bargains that are serving to minimize and even invisibilize from the official record of what actually took place that day, in what ws an outright attempt to derail the official certification of the election. Worse, it is actually still taking place right before our very eyes. Instead of dealing with it as such, it is being treated akin to fraternity pranks gone awry, with unfounded challenges to the 2020 election continuing to this day. The plea bargains, which have been reduced to barely misdemeanors, have resulted in no jail or prison time for the majority of these criminal insurrectionists. To be remembered is that the insurrectionists, virtually all of them white, were not apprehended that day. That reinforces why many people do not believe in the fairness of the nation‚Äôs systems of law; whether it is law enforcement agencies, the judicial or the prison system. There are lots of reasons why people hold these views, including after the country witnessed: ‚Ä¢ Dylan Roof killing nine African American parishioners in Charleston, North Carolina in 2015, and then actually being treated to a free Burger King meal by law enforcement. ‚Ä¢ Patrick Crusius shooting and killing 23 people and injuring 23 others, in El Paso, Texas in 2019, and then being arrested without incident. ‚Ä¢ Kyle Rittenhouse shooting two protestors in Kenosha, Wisconsin in 2020, then walking right past officers unmolested. In contrast, how many killings do we know of, involving people of color who within seconds are killed by law enforcement officers, for doing nothing except being Red-Black-Brown? It is not a small number. Think 12-year-old Tamir Rice with a toy rifle killed in Cleveland in 2014. Think 72-year old Francisco Serna, killed in Bakersfield Calif, in 2016, with crucifix in hand. column30: The Song of the Quetzal http://www.populist.com/27.20.Cintli.htm (Vea la versi√≥n en espa√±ol a continuaci√≥n. By Dr CINTLI Last month, I went to a funeral in Los Angeles for the father of three friends of mine who were tortured in the early 1980s when they were high school students in Guatemala. They survived because their father, Jose Domingo Perez, waged a heroic nationwide campaign to secure their release, this during the first month of a genocidal terror campaign immediately after a military coup by General Jose Efrain Rios Montt. This was during Guatemala‚Äôs 30-year genocidal war at which time its generals boasted that they held no political prisoners. They even refused US military aid, so as to not be constrained by US ‚Äúrules,‚Äù this when it was the chief sponsor of Central America‚Äôs wars. The war was waged by a series of military regimes, against primarily Indigenous peoples, that once capturing their ‚Äúenemies,‚Äù tortured and executed them. During that war, hundreds of thousands were killed and perhaps an equal number ‚Äúdisappeared.‚Äù Several million were also internally and externally displaced. At the funeral, I recalled a 1981 story I had written: ‚ÄúThe Song of the Quetzal,‚Äù reminding me of how I met my friends. I had gone to see ‚ÄúWhen the Mountains Tremble,‚Äù which is about that war, as told by Rigoberta Menchu, who lost both her parents during the war, and who in 1992 would go on to receive the Nobel Peace Prize. Afterwards, I told them about that story, basically about how it cannot live in captivity, an allegory about that ruthless war. As a result, they invited me to their next meeting. I was so moved that for the next several years, I attended virtually all their meetings. They were primarily young ex-students; most of whom were younger than me, but not all. Many of them were student activists during the war, some of whom had been captured during protests. When my friends were apprehended, about 10 other students were executed before their very eyes with about 15 more being captured and then tortured. They never spoke about those details. Being intrigued, I was told to watch the movie ‚ÄúEl Norte‚Äù; that what happened to the Perez family, was worse than what was depicted (Domingo was actually in it). After watching it, I got the nerve to ask one of the sisters, Noemi, what had happened to her. ‚ÄúEverything that could be done to a woman was done to me for 15 days,‚Äù she told me. I never brought up the topic again. Eventually, they received political asylum, an extreme rarity in those days. After years of no contact, during the 2013 Rios Montt trial ‚Äî who was eventually convicted of genocide and crimes against humanity, but later won on appeal ‚Äî they told me that they also had their own case against the government. They showed me their testimonies and told me they were looking for someone they trusted to translate them into English. Without hesitation, I volunteered. I assumed their torture was extreme, but nothing could have prepared me for what I read, despite myself being a survivor of state violence, diagnosed with PTSD and Traumatic Brain Injury. To this day, their testimonies haunt me. I had no idea the depravity humans are capable of. What most stood out was their constant pleas to be executed, rather than undergo their nightmarish torture, though they were always awake. The funeral made me recall all this, especially their father‚Äôs role. I left the funeral believing that his pleas were indeed the Song of the Quetzal; the story I had written was about my friends I had not yet met. It was both a story and song, about Guatemala‚Äôs war, as brutal as that of the genocidal Spanish ‚Äúconquest.‚Äù Here are the last lines to the song: For many years, we have been peaceful. But now, they no longer leave us alone. We are pure fury, ready to confront those that have forced us to hide. We are not alone. Today, it is the Quetzal. Tomorrow the Condor. And the next day the Eagle. Do not be blind. Can you not see? It is you who I sing for. You are the Quetzal. The song was published in my 2021 ‚ÄúWriting 50 Years Amongst the Gringos‚Äù book, but the story has been lost to time, though it will be published eventually, even if I have to recreate it, in Spanish, English and in one of the Maya languages, as I initially promised them. I also remember that I gave Noemi a pre-Colombian statue, instructing her to return it to me when her country is free. We all joked after the funeral, knowing that won‚Äôt be happening anytime soon. Despite the traumatic memories, the only sad part of the funeral is that Marvyn, stricken by COVID, could not attend his father‚Äôs funeral. Jose Domingo Perez. Presente! Roberto Dr. Cintli Rodriguez is an associate professor emeritus at the University of Arizona Mexican American Studies and is the author of several books, including ‚ÄúOur Sacred Maiz is Our Mother‚Äù (2014), ‚ÄúYolqui: A Warrior Summoned from the Spirit World‚Äù (2019) and ‚ÄúWriting 50 years Amongst the Gringos,‚Äù published recently by (truncated)

A copy of the letter we sent in to our MP & MPP‚Ä¶. Good afternoon, I am one of your constituents in Stittsville and wanted to write to you in order to inform you of at least one ""ground level"" story of how the lockdowns are affecting the public. My family is struggling already and I don't know if another lockdown period is going to be sustainable. My wife and I both work for the federal government and have been rather unaffected by the lockdowns income-wise, luckily, however the school and other closures are taking a huge toll on my children. I have two in high school and one in grade 6 and all of them have seen their social circles evaporate in the past two years. The lockdown has hit them socially extremely hard as they struggled making friends beforehand, but now they all have none. I try to get them to enter other activities however everything is closed. Each time we start gaining momentum, we get the rug pulled out from under us. They have lost their drive and they are always sad. All have developed anxiety issues and are now seeing counsellors, their grades are suffering and we are struggling more and more to keep them moving forward in life. My eldest in particular has lost half of grade nine, all of grade 10 and it looks like all of grade 11. She will have lost her entire high school life and lost all social contacts being locked in her room by society order. I don't think that we can handle another lockdown. Several times a week we are consoling at least one of them as they cry themselves to sleep. My children NEED to be able to go to school and develop socially. We need help! To be clear I'm not an internet troll anti-vaxxer, we are all fully vaccinated. I fail to understand with all the research coming out that the omicron variant is far less serious than the original covid virus, why we are being pushed to the breaking point again. I know the story that the hospitals *might* be overwhelmed, but from my standpoint it seems like my family and I are being forced to *actually* suffer so that someone else *might* not. We keep being told to ""suck it up"" but we've been doing everything *right* this whole time but the finish line keeps getting moved further and further away and we have reached our breaking point. Even my entire extended family is becoming quite extremist and it's scary. My uncles, aunts and cousins are turning anti-vax, crowing about 5G and Q-anon conspiracy theories and they are getting louder. These restrictions are causing something very ugly to bubble to the surface in our society. Please, we need your help to make our voices heard. Best Regards, Giles Babin and Family
